news.title: Builders in Jharkhand grapple with skyrocketing sand prices
news.para: Vikash Vijayvargia, a city-based contractor who builds overhead water tanks for state govt in the city and across the district, claimed that sand shortage have forced work to come to a halt for nearly four months now.

news.title: Ummeed Housing Finance raises Rs 630 crore equity
news.para: Ummeed Housing Finance raises ₹630 crore in Series F round from investors including A91 Partners LLP and existing investors. Funds to be used for expansion in central and southern India.

news.title: CCI approves Godrej Group's internal restructuring
news.para: Under the terms of the FSA, the realignment will encompass entities like the GILAC Group Entities and G&B group entities, marking a strategic effort to streamline operations and consolidate governance structures within the conglomerate.

news.title: CCI approves proposed stake acquisition in WeWork India by Real Trustee Advisory
news.para: Embassy Buildcon is engaged in the business of real estate development of residential and commercial assets and other related activities.

news.title: SC stays criminal proceedings against Ireo' MD & Oberoi Realty's chairman
news.para: The question as to whether the filing of the second complaint would amount to an abuse of process and as to whether the complainant approached the Court with unclean hands requires further examination, the apex court said.

news.title: YEIDA may partially cancel land allotments to ATS Realty & Supertech Township Project
news.para: ATS Realty, which has constructed Allure on much of the land, has outstanding dues of Rs 668 crore. The housing society has around 1,800 residents. Supertech, which is building Golf Country involving 3,200 buyers, owes Rs 677 crore to YEIDA.

news.title: Construction equipment industry expects cost pinch of around 15% due to new CEV-V regulations
news.para: India’s construction equipment industry has been growing at a health double digit trot year on year.

news.title: Abhishek Bachchan buys six apartments in Mumbai’s Borivali suburb
news.para: Bachchan has acquired these apartments spread over 4,894 sq ft on the 57th floor of luxury project Oberoi Sky City from the company’s subsidiary Incline Realty at Rs 31,498 per sq ft.

news.title: Lennar's home delivery forecast falls short of estimate
news.para: With the popular 30-year fixed mortgage rate currently at a two-decade high of nearly 7%, existing housing supply also remains tight as a majority of homeowners are unwilling to resell their homes, having locked down home loan rates below 5% during an era of cheap debt.

news.title: China's property measures give sales a boost, but only in big cities
news.para: On May 17, China cut minimum mortgage rates and downpayments and instructed municipalities to buy unsold apartments to turn them into social housing, sparking dozens of announcements from cities easing policies under the new guidelines.

news.title: Home building permits in Germany fall by 17% in April 2024
news.para: Some 17,600 permits were issued, which is 17% fewer than a year earlier, the data showed, making for a nearly 44% drop over the past two years.

news.title: Housing rent grows by 2-4% in top seven cities in Q2 2024: Anarock
news.para: The average rent for a standard 1,000 square feet 2-BHK apartment in Bengaluru's Whitefield rose by 4 per cent to Rs 35,000 per month in Q2 2024 to date from Rs 32,500 per month in January-March this year.

news.title: Ghaziabad extracted 123% of water it recharged last year, highest in Uttar Pradesh
news.para: Ghaziabad is facing a plummeting groundwater level due to rapid industrialization and a population boom, with the city extracting 123% of its total groundwater last year, the highest in the state.

news.title: ESR Group buys 27-acre land in Chennai for Rs 276 crore
news.para: The additional Rs 276 crore (over USD 33 million) investment signifies ESR's dedication to bolstering Tamil Nadu's industrial landscape," the company said in a statement on Monday.

news.title: Indirapuram may be handed over to Ghaziabad civic body in July
news.para: A joint survey by the corporation (GMC) and GDA is in the final stages and cost estimates will be drawn up shortly, which will pave the way for the handover.

news.title: Godrej Industries’ chairman, family buys three flats for Rs 180 crore in South Mumbai
news.para: The under-construction super-luxury residential project, Ruparel House, on Ridge Road at the top of Malabar Hill with the view of Queen’s Necklace, is being developed by R House Realty, part of JSW Realty.

news.title: Asking prices for UK houses stagnate in June: Rightmove
news.para: The company said the average asking price was 375,110 pounds ($475,827) for property put on sale between May 12 and June 8, down 21 pounds from a month earlier and statistically a flat reading.

news.title: China’s central bank keeps lending rate unchanged
news.para: The government reported Monday that factory output fell 5.6% in May from the year before, slowing from 6.7% in April, though analysts noted some impact due to more work days in this year compared with the year before.

news.title: New home prices in China fall 3.9% year-on-year in May 2024
news.para: Prices were down 0.7% in May from the previous month, marking the 11th straight month-on-month decline and steepest drop since October 2014, according to Reuters calculations based on National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) data.

news.title: Oyo in advance talks to raise Rs 1,000 crore
news.para: Oyo fundraise: Hospitality startup Oyo is raising around Rs 1,000 crore from family offices and investors. The fundraise aims to value Oyo at about $2.5 billion, marking a significant decrease from its peak valuation of $9 billion in 2021.
